<h2 id="_naming_the_domain">3. Naming the domain</h2>
<div class="sectionbody">
<div class="olist arabic">
<ol class="arabic">
<li>
<p><a href="#50">Open the domain assistant</a> and navigate to the step <strong>Name the domain</strong>.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Enter the desired domain name.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Select the appropriate domain options. Expand the info box below (<span class="icon darkGrey"><i class="fa fa-chevron-down  "></i></span>) if you need additional information about one of the options.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Ready to continue? Click on <strong>Next</strong> <span class="icon blue"><i class="fa fa-angle-right  "></i></span></p>
</li>
</ol>
</div>
<div class="openblock collapseBox">
<div class="title"><strong>Additional information about the individual options</strong></div>
<div class="content">
<div class="paragraph">
<p>Which settings are displayed here depends on which <a href="#100">type of domain</a> you selected in the previous step.</p>
</div>
<table id="table-assistant-domains-names" class="tableblock frame-all grid-all stretch">
<colgroup>
<col style="width: 25%;">
<col style="width: 75%;">
</colgroup>
